    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6fff696c_75a1fbeb",
        "filename": "android/cmdline-option_unittest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 134,
      "author": {
        "id": 1099352
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-27T17:10:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How about this: cmdline-option.c has a second .h file, cmdline-option-testing.h.  It still has debug_tags (which is static, not global), but it introduces a pointer variable, initialized to point at the start of this array.  We use that everywhere as we currently use debug_tags.  cmdline_option_testing.h exposes \"set_debug_tags\" and \"restore_debug_tags\", which set/restore this pointer variable.  This allows a test to control the set of defined tags, to allow a hermetic test.\n\nI think we need to be more willing to make some concession to private test-only interfaces to enable good unit tests.",
      "parentUuid": "0fd8ad39_5f240b19",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 134,
        "startChar": 11,
        "endLine": 134,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "b1b6acb2251db92f2d899ea9871f9d86b93cc400",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
